2026-05-11 | Palindrome Pair in Array of Strings

	Question
Return true if any valid pair exists.
	Key Insight
For two strings to form palindrome:
		one side often mirrors the other  
A simple and effective approach:
		try all pairs and check palindrome.
	Approach
1.	Define helper function:
		check if string is palindrome  
2.	Try every pair (i, j):
		where i ≠ j  
3.	Concatenate:
		arr[i] + arr[j]  
4.	If palindrome found:
		return true  
5.	If no pair works:
		return false  
	Time Complexity
	O(n² × L)
	where L = average string length
	Space Complexity
	O(L)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    bool isPalindrome(string &s){
        int l = 0;
        int r = s.size() - 1;
        while(l < r){
            if(s[l] != s[r])
                return false;
            l++;
            r--;
        }
        return true;
    }
    bool palindromepair(vector<string>& arr) {
        int n = arr.size();
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++){
            for(int j = 0; j < n; j++){
                if(i == j) continue;
                string temp = arr[i] + arr[j];
                if(isPalindrome(temp))
                    return true;
            }
        }
        return false;
    }
};
	Key Insight
The problem directly asks about:
		pairwise concatenation behavior  
So brute-force pair checking with palindrome validation
is straightforward and reliable.
